41:53.376 --> 41:55.376
Yeah.

41:55.694 --> 41:57.694
How have you been?

41:58.022 --> 41:59.190
I'm fine.

41:59.290 --> 42:01.290
How are you?

42:01.382 --> 42:03.382
Yeah, good.

42:03.609 --> 42:05.609
Are these your kids?

42:06.372 --> 42:08.372
Yeah.

42:14.147 --> 42:16.737
Well, I'll see you around.

42:18.326 --> 42:19.734
Yeah, uh...

42:19.834 --> 42:21.834
I'll see you around.

42:33.071 --> 42:38.251
What on Earth made me say,
'I don't go swimming with idiots'?

43:06.423 --> 43:08.133
You're going to swim?

43:08.233 --> 43:11.293
Come on, the water's nice.
- No, I...

43:15.695 --> 43:17.711
I don't know how to swim.

43:17.811 --> 43:19.811
Sorry?

43:20.503 --> 43:22.628
I don't know how to swim.

43:23.729 --> 43:25.729
That's it.

43:26.565 --> 43:28.690
Please don't tell anyone.

43:30.468 --> 43:32.641
Hey, aren't you gonna swim?

43:32.741 --> 43:35.942
No, I've got my period.
I'm gonna stay here.

43:36.042 --> 43:37.827
Nemo will keep me company.

43:37.927 --> 43:39.927
Okay.

44:08.300 --> 44:13.009
Darling? I... I want to
introduce you to someone.

44:13.193 --> 44:15.566
You've already met Harry.
- Hey.

44:15.666 --> 44:20.416
And this is his daughter, Anna.
Anna, this is Nemo.

44:30.889 --> 44:33.099
Why don't you shake hands?

44:51.903 --> 44:53.903
How was work today?

45:14.080 --> 45:16.788
Ugh, I can't believe them.

45:16.789 --> 45:19.679
Soon as I wonder how old they are.

45:23.009 --> 45:25.174
They already slept together?

45:25.274 --> 45:27.274
I don't know.

45:27.801 --> 45:28.876
I hope they use condoms.

45:28.976 --> 45:32.886
I do not want to end up with a little brother.

45:33.622 --> 45:35.255
I'd rather die.

45:35.355 --> 45:37.355
Is you mom on the pill?

45:38.295 --> 45:40.295
I have no idea.

45:41.092 --> 45:43.403
We should slip it into her morning coffee.

45:43.503 --> 45:47.243
It's like her hormones
have gone to her head.

45:52.139 --> 45:54.774
Sometimes I can see the future.

45:56.743 --> 46:02.693
It doesn't seem like it can be much fun
knowing what's going to happen.

46:21.980 --> 46:24.334
You're still here.

46:25.967 --> 46:28.793
Did I fall asleep?

46:30.411 --> 46:33.824
Sometimes I don't sleep.

46:35.215 --> 46:37.215
So I think...

46:39.252 --> 46:42.195
I think about how it was.

46:44.552 --> 46:47.260
It's all I have left.

46:50.988 --> 46:54.167
What do you see when you look at me?

46:54.383 --> 46:58.716
A grumpy old man
who never answers questions?

46:58.751 --> 47:00.953
Who mixes everything up?

47:01.935 --> 47:06.999
Who is kept busy by getting his meals?

47:08.723 --> 47:11.077
Now that's not me...

47:14.368 --> 47:16.368
Me...

47:18.142 --> 47:20.261
I wear shorts.

47:22.423 --> 47:25.484
I'm nine years old.

47:27.035 --> 47:30.567
I can run faster than the train.

47:33.127 --> 47:37.012
I can't feel my aching back anymore.

47:38.858 --> 47:40.860
I'm 15.

47:43.654 --> 47:45.772
I'm 15.

47:47.561 --> 47:49.680
And I'm in love.

47:52.549 --> 47:54.549
I'm in love.

49:17.319 --> 49:19.319
Nemo?

49:19.876 --> 49:21.876
Nemo?

49:24.224 --> 49:26.224
Nemo?

49:32.012 --> 49:34.277
Isn't he sleeping in the study?

49:34.377 --> 49:37.288
No, I just looked and he isn't there.

49:37.388 --> 49:42.063
Anna, have you seen your brother?
- He's not my brother.

49:51.213 --> 49:53.933
Oh, there you are.
Sleep alright?

50:18.401 --> 50:20.756
Who's that?
- It's me.

50:22.932 --> 50:24.308
It's me, Dad...

50:24.408 --> 50:26.223
Nemo.

50:26.323 --> 50:28.036
Your son.

50:28.136 --> 50:30.136
Of course, son.

50:30.413 --> 50:33.710
Where were you?
- At the shop, Dad.

50:34.506 --> 50:36.242
I always work at the shop after school.

50:36.342 --> 50:40.817
You know, a boy your age
should get out more.

50:40.852 --> 50:44.031
You can leave me alone, you know.
I-I can manage.

50:44.131 --> 50:46.131
It's no problem, Dad.

50:46.588 --> 50:48.588
I like being at home.

51:17.846 --> 51:21.564
There was a card
from your mother in the post.

51:21.664 --> 51:25.685
You have not read it.
- I know. I'll read it later.

51:25.785 --> 51:28.590
Won't you go and see her one day?

51:28.642 --> 51:31.067
I haven't seen her in seven years.

51:31.167 --> 51:36.012
If she ever wanted to see me,
she'd know where to find me.

51:37.691 --> 51:40.180
I've got everything I need, Dad.

51:40.280 --> 51:42.280
Everything's fine.

52:16.381 --> 52:18.500
After three months,

52:18.779 --> 52:21.016
and six days of travel...

52:24.342 --> 52:26.807
...the shuttle was heading...

52:27.947 --> 52:31.715
...directly toward the Cancer nebula...

52:33.295 --> 52:35.767
...in line with Uranus...

52:37.482 --> 52:39.482
...and its five moons.

53:00.405 --> 53:04.400
It was finally aproaching
Mars and the Colonies.

53:08.936 --> 53:10.936
Onboard...

53:11.107 --> 53:16.887
...the computer was monitoring
the passengers' artificial hibernation

53:32.231 --> 53:34.231
Elise.

55:09.974 --> 55:11.974
I'm not crazy.

55:12.170 --> 55:13.868
Come on,
it's not that bad.

55:13.968 --> 55:16.876
I didn't say anything mean.

55:19.190 --> 55:21.190
Shall we go, Nemo?

55:21.426 --> 55:24.996
Excuse me?
- Shall we go? He's such a bore.

55:44.918 --> 55:46.918
You'll drown.

55:51.475 --> 55:55.948
How do you know my name?
- We go to the same school.

55:56.808 --> 56:00.633
You never noticed me.
You never notice anyone.

56:06.379 --> 56:08.419
D'you have a girlfriend?

56:10.566 --> 56:13.965
What? Are you queer?
Why don't you have a girlfriend?

56:14.065 --> 56:16.065
I don't know...

56:16.402 --> 56:18.402
I-I don't want one.

56:20.789 --> 56:22.789
Tell me about yourself.

56:26.000 --> 56:30.382
You used to piss your pants,
everyone knows you're weirdo.

56:30.482 --> 56:32.482
You're always alone...

56:35.813 --> 56:37.813
Talk.

56:39.786 --> 56:42.081
Or say something.
Come on...

56:47.565 --> 56:50.861
Gravity on Mars is 0.38.

56:53.808 --> 56:57.038
That's three times less than on Earth.

56:58.251 --> 57:02.255
The ground is covered
with an iron oxide dust.

57:10.302 --> 57:12.302
You're incredible.

57:14.242 --> 57:17.775
Raise your hand and say 'I swear.'
- Why?

57:18.118 --> 57:22.878
Promise me that if I die,
you'll spread my ashes on Mars.

57:23.582 --> 57:27.047
It's estimated that travel to Mars
would take six to eight months.

57:27.147 --> 57:29.147
Say 'I swear.'

57:32.741 --> 57:34.741
I swear.

57:38.814 --> 57:42.044
We were neighbors when we were little.

57:44.129 --> 57:45.996
It's Elise.

57:46.096 --> 57:48.096
Don't you remember?

57:48.172 --> 57:50.172
Elise.

57:50.312 --> 57:52.311
I had a feeling I've seen you or something.

57:52.411 --> 57:54.203
Yeah, that's called deja vu.

57:54.303 --> 57:57.260
And the signal from the eyes
goes from the memory...

57:57.360 --> 57:59.360
No, it's not it.

58:00.185 --> 58:02.185
Another life then?

58:03.238 --> 58:05.238
Anyway...

58:05.785 --> 58:07.785
I remembered you.

58:20.873 --> 58:22.420
We shouldn't.

58:22.520 --> 58:25.821
You don't know me
and I am not a good person.

58:25.921 --> 58:27.921
Why do you say that?

58:50.116 --> 58:52.587
Elise, wait.
- I'll call you.

58:52.643 --> 58:55.278
You don't have my phone number.

58:57.477 --> 59:00.367
What happens when we fall in love?

59:01.290 --> 59:04.470
As a result of certain stimuli,

59:04.471 --> 59:08.632
the hypothalamus releases
a powerful discharges of endorphins...

59:08.732 --> 59:12.980
...but why exactly that woman or that man?

59:13.015 --> 59:15.719
Is there a release of
odourless pheromones...

59:15.819 --> 59:18.922
...that correspond to
our complimentary genetic signal?

59:19.022 --> 59:22.477
Or is it physical feutures
that we recognize?

59:22.577 --> 59:24.662
A mother's eyes...

59:25.310 --> 59:28.625
A smell that stimulates a happy memory.

59:29.532 --> 59:33.298
Is love...
part of a plan?

59:33.383 --> 59:37.622
A vast war plan
between two modes of reproduction

59:37.682 --> 59:41.820
Bacteria and viruses
are asexual organisms.

59:41.855 --> 59:44.559
With each cell division,
each multiplication,

59:44.659 --> 59:47.571
they mutate and perfect themselves
much more quickly than we do.

59:47.671 --> 59:52.313
Against this, we respond
with the most fiercing weapon:

59:52.348 --> 59:54.089
Sex.

59:54.189 --> 59:57.291
Two individuals,
by mixing their genes,

59:57.391 --> 1:00:02.874
shuffle the cards and create an individual
who resists viruses better.

1:00:02.974 --> 1:00:05.561
The more disimilar he or she is.

1:00:05.661 --> 1:00:12.206
Now, are we unknowing participants in
a war between two modes of reproduction?

1:00:15.400 --> 1:00:18.290
Okay everyone,
that's it for today.

1:00:20.288 --> 1:00:22.031
How was it?

1:00:22.131 --> 1:00:24.104
You want to know the truth?

1:00:24.204 --> 1:00:27.519
O'key. It was good. It was really good.

1:00:29.822 --> 1:00:32.038
Hey, honey.
- I'm gonna be a little late.

1:00:32.138 --> 1:00:34.263
That's okay. Don't worry.

1:00:34.380 --> 1:00:37.088
I love you.
- I love you more.

1:00:37.089 --> 1:00:39.089
Me more.
- Me more.

1:00:39.096 --> 1:00:41.215
Okay
- Cheater.

1:00:41.979 --> 1:00:44.274
Alright, I'll see ya later.

1:01:44.530 --> 1:01:47.003
I always liked fish.

1:01:47.101 --> 1:01:51.436
I never thought that one day
they would like me too.

1:01:53.453 --> 1:01:55.453
You're very relaxed.

1:01:56.822 --> 1:02:00.000
Your eyelids are getting heavy.

1:02:01.177 --> 1:02:03.178
Remember.

1:02:04.619 --> 1:02:06.619
Remember...

1:02:11.830 --> 1:02:14.066
Remember...

1:03:18.381 --> 1:03:19.282
Nemo...

1:03:19.382 --> 1:03:19.828
Shit.

1:03:19.928 --> 1:03:21.928
Anna...

1:03:23.727 --> 1:03:27.722
We've got errands to run.
We'll back in an hour.

1:03:29.883 --> 1:03:34.005
Anna, cover up.
You're gonna get a sunburn.

1:04:52.248 --> 1:04:54.248
I want you.

1:04:55.115 --> 1:04:57.115
I want you too.

1:04:58.951 --> 1:05:00.951
Forever.

1:05:03.217 --> 1:05:05.217
Forever.

1:05:05.387 --> 1:05:07.387
Whatever happens.

1:05:07.782 --> 1:05:10.247
There is no life without you.

1:05:10.733 --> 1:05:12.733
No life without you.

1:05:36.510 --> 1:05:38.510
You look like my son.

1:05:39.569 --> 1:05:41.569
I am your son, Dad.

1:05:41.888 --> 1:05:44.013
My son's taller than you.

1:05:59.733 --> 1:06:01.733
Elise

1:07:05.843 --> 1:07:07.843
Someone just came in.

1:07:09.118 --> 1:07:12.415
If I could at least move my fingers.

1:07:13.633 --> 1:07:15.633
Or my eyes.

1:07:16.728 --> 1:07:19.108
Do you think he can hear us?

1:07:19.350 --> 1:07:21.135
Have you seen any reaction?

1:07:21.235 --> 1:07:22.776
I don't know, but...

1:07:22.876 --> 1:07:24.543
I've got a feeling that he can.

1:07:24.643 --> 1:07:25.941
Who's there?

1:07:26.041 --> 1:07:27.761
What am I doing here?

1:07:27.861 --> 1:07:30.405
If you can hear me,
move your fingers.

1:07:30.505 --> 1:07:31.817
I've got to get out of here.

1:07:31.917 --> 1:07:34.390
Go back,
before the accident.

1:08:05.160 --> 1:08:07.160
I believe one thing.

1:08:09.196 --> 1:08:15.146
I believe that we should always say
'I love you' to the people we love.

1:08:21.887 --> 1:08:23.887
I love you.

1:08:31.026 --> 1:08:34.557
Nemo... we shouldn't.

1:08:36.189 --> 1:08:38.189
I love Stefano.

1:08:39.121 --> 1:08:40.729
What?

1:08:40.829 --> 1:08:43.634
You saw him at the party with me.

1:08:45.384 --> 1:08:47.384
He doesn't love me.

1:08:48.714 --> 1:08:49.299
And so...

1:08:49.399 --> 1:08:51.399
I love him anyways.

1:08:51.458 --> 1:08:53.458
I can't help myself.

1:08:54.163 --> 1:08:56.163
I'm in love with him.

1:08:58.374 --> 1:09:00.374
I'm sorry.

1:09:12.065 --> 1:09:13.745
Dad, I'm getting married.

1:09:13.845 --> 1:09:15.132
Oh.

1:09:15.232 --> 1:09:17.242
And who is the lucky lady?

1:09:17.342 --> 1:09:19.342
No, it's not that.

1:09:19.977 --> 1:09:24.822
I'm gonna marry the first girl
who dances with me tonight.

1:10:01.092 --> 1:10:03.092
Thanks, Nemo.

1:10:39.735 --> 1:10:41.735
Nemo.

1:10:46.864 --> 1:10:51.284
On that day, I would make
a lot of foolish decisions.

1:10:52.275 --> 1:10:55.590
One, I will never
leave anything to chance again.

1:10:55.690 --> 1:10:58.914
Two, I will marry the girl on my motorcycle.

1:10:59.014 --> 1:11:01.014
Three, I'll be rich.

1:11:01.102 --> 1:11:03.227
Four, we'll have a house.

1:11:03.262 --> 1:11:04.429
A big house.

1:11:04.529 --> 1:11:06.671
Painted yellow,
with a garden,

1:11:06.771 --> 1:11:09.108
and two children,
Paul and Michael.

1:11:09.208 --> 1:11:12.716
Five, I'll have a convertible--
A red convertible.

1:11:12.816 --> 1:11:15.297
And a swimming pool.
I'll learn to swim.

1:11:15.397 --> 1:11:19.399
Six, I will not stop until I've succeeded.

1:11:40.560 --> 1:11:42.560
Daddy?

1:11:44.089 --> 1:11:46.089
Daddy?

1:11:49.498 --> 1:11:51.963
Paul, don't wake your father.

1:11:52.398 --> 1:11:53.926
Elise?

1:11:54.026 --> 1:11:56.026
It's me, Jean.

1:11:58.308 --> 1:12:00.308
Who is Elise?

1:12:03.495 --> 1:12:05.982
I don't know anyone called Elise.

1:12:06.082 --> 1:12:08.082
Go back and play Paul.

1:12:10.731 --> 1:12:13.439
Nemo, do I matter to you?

1:12:17.214 --> 1:12:18.290
I just...

1:12:18.390 --> 1:12:21.450
I just like to ask you one question.

1:12:22.335 --> 1:12:24.460
Did you do it on purpose?

1:12:27.322 --> 1:12:30.212
I found this on the bedside table.

1:12:31.065 --> 1:12:35.347
There comes a time in life
when everything seems narrow.

1:12:35.447 --> 1:12:40.121
Choices have been made
I can only continue on.

1:12:40.430 --> 1:12:43.745
I know myself like the back of my hand.

1:12:44.537 --> 1:12:47.145
I can predict my every reaction.

1:12:47.245 --> 1:12:49.455
Everything is predictable.

1:12:49.550 --> 1:12:54.278
My life has been cast in cement
with airbags and seatbelts.

1:12:54.378 --> 1:12:56.217
I've controlled everything.

1:12:56.317 --> 1:13:01.061
I've done everything to reach
this point and now that I'm here,

1:13:01.161 --> 1:13:03.280
I'm fucking bored.

1:13:05.428 --> 1:13:09.848
The hardest thing is knowing
whether I'm still alive.

1:13:16.517 --> 1:13:18.753
It is my handwriting.

1:13:19.968 --> 1:13:21.969
I don't remember.

1:13:39.547 --> 1:13:41.547
Jean?

1:13:44.319 --> 1:13:46.319
What did you say?

1:13:49.436 --> 1:13:51.436
I had a weird dream.

1:14:11.134 --> 1:14:14.242
Well, it's important for you to understand.

1:14:14.342 --> 1:14:17.958
In life things don't always turn out...

1:14:18.532 --> 1:14:20.532
...as we plan them.

1:14:21.097 --> 1:14:23.097
Harry and I thought...

1:14:25.397 --> 1:14:28.141
Life isn't what we all think it will be.

1:14:28.241 --> 1:14:30.536
What are you talking about?

1:14:31.496 --> 1:14:33.496
I don't understand.

1:14:33.903 --> 1:14:35.903
Anna knows already.

1:14:38.615 --> 1:14:41.505
Harry and I are going to separate.

1:14:42.681 --> 1:14:44.681
What?

1:14:45.311 --> 1:14:47.311
Why?

1:14:48.266 --> 1:14:51.945
You have no right.
- Please, you played your part.

1:14:52.045 --> 1:14:54.076
I don't know what is going on
between you two...

1:14:54.176 --> 1:14:56.678
...and I don't wanna know.
It's sick.

1:14:56.778 --> 1:15:03.068
You're brother and sister, for God's sake.
- We are not brother and sister.

1:15:08.804 --> 1:15:10.804
You knew.

1:15:11.564 --> 1:15:13.564
And you didn't tell me.

1:15:21.010 --> 1:15:23.010
Where are you going?

1:15:25.145 --> 1:15:27.145
To New York.

1:15:28.804 --> 1:15:31.040
In ten days.

1:15:32.578 --> 1:15:34.958
My father found a job there.

1:15:45.052 --> 1:15:47.942
Wait for me near the lighthouse...

1:15:48.015 --> 1:15:50.135
...every Sunday, okay?

1:15:51.886 --> 1:15:54.246
Until we see each other again.

1:15:54.346 --> 1:15:56.582
For life, okay?

1:16:00.226 --> 1:16:02.226
It's not over.

1:16:09.584 --> 1:16:13.664
You're the first and last person I'll ever love.

1:16:14.876 --> 1:16:16.876
Ten days.

1:16:18.487 --> 1:16:20.487
That makes...

1:16:21.136 --> 1:16:23.136
...14 thousand...

1:16:23.692 --> 1:16:25.692
...400 minutes.

1:16:29.629 --> 1:16:32.944
I wish everything would stop right now.

1:16:34.636 --> 1:16:37.611
Things would stay this way forever.

1:16:39.877 --> 1:16:43.532
They say that if you slow your breathing...

1:16:43.872 --> 1:16:45.872
...time slows down.

1:16:47.699 --> 1:16:49.699
The Hindu say so.

1:17:30.279 --> 1:17:34.954
I have to remember the smell
of every part of your body.

1:17:44.481 --> 1:17:47.116
We'll meet near the lighthouse.

1:18:10.301 --> 1:18:12.303
Anna, it's time to go.

1:18:22.686 --> 1:18:24.686
I love you.

1:19:07.983 --> 1:19:10.926
Anna.

1:19:46.536 --> 1:19:48.536
Anna...

1:19:48.539 --> 1:19:50.539
Can you hear me?

1:20:12.406 --> 1:20:14.701
We must look to the future.

1:20:14.976 --> 1:20:17.147
It will be good to move house.

1:20:17.247 --> 1:20:19.247
Have a new life.

1:20:19.474 --> 1:20:21.474
Will we have a pool?

1:20:21.695 --> 1:20:24.670
You hate water.
You don't even swim.

1:20:24.843 --> 1:20:27.719
You never know what you want.
- You know what I don't want?

1:20:27.819 --> 1:20:31.049
So tell me, what is it you don't want?

1:20:32.876 --> 1:20:35.256
I don't want to be like you.

1:20:37.344 --> 1:20:39.554
You know nothing about me.

1:20:40.227 --> 1:20:42.267
I've always loved pools.

1:20:44.387 --> 1:20:47.107
When I'm older,
I'll have a pool.

1:21:42.055 --> 1:21:44.055
Anna.

1:21:44.756 --> 1:21:46.756
Anna.

1:21:47.642 --> 1:21:52.147
I feel like I'll be seeing you
at every street corner.

1:22:13.214 --> 1:22:15.687
Sometimes I tell myself...

1:22:16.376 --> 1:22:19.180
...maybe you live in the same town I do...

1:22:19.280 --> 1:22:21.279
...and I don't know where.

1:22:21.379 --> 1:22:24.558
Maybe you're here,
very close.

1:22:25.240 --> 1:22:28.654
Nemo, do you hear my voice?

1:22:30.730 --> 1:22:32.730
Anna.

