1:36:59.056 --> 1:37:02.046
I said I would never love anyone else.

1:37:02.146 --> 1:37:04.146
Ever.

1:37:04.366 --> 1:37:06.731
I would never become attached.

1:37:06.831 --> 1:37:09.174
I'd never see you put anywhere.

1:37:09.274 --> 1:37:11.654
I'd have nothing for myself.

1:37:14.564 --> 1:37:18.332
I decided I would pretend to be alive.

1:37:23.332 --> 1:37:26.148
And this is what I've been waiting for.

1:37:26.248 --> 1:37:28.249
All this time...

1:37:30.266 --> 1:37:35.329
Renouncing all possible lives,
for one only...

1:37:36.430 --> 1:37:38.430
With you.

1:37:47.516 --> 1:37:50.151
But I'm not used to it anymore.

1:37:51.024 --> 1:37:54.847
you know... love... I mean.

1:37:58.719 --> 1:38:01.354
I'm afraid of losing you again,

1:38:01.443 --> 1:38:04.402
I'm afraid of having to do without you again

1:38:04.502 --> 1:38:05.956
I...

1:38:06.056 --> 1:38:08.056
I'm terrified of that.

1:38:13.060 --> 1:38:15.185
We need to take some time

1:38:16.250 --> 1:38:18.885
And, when will I see you again?

1:38:26.062 --> 1:38:28.187
Call me at this number...

1:38:31.362 --> 1:38:33.362
...in two days

1:38:36.845 --> 1:38:39.565
I'll meet you at the lighthouse.

1:39:21.846 --> 1:39:24.788
You know why I lost Anna?

1:39:26.418 --> 1:39:28.889
because two months earlier

1:39:29.186 --> 1:39:32.571
An unployed Brazilian boiled an egg

1:39:38.336 --> 1:39:42.380
The heat created a
micro-climate in the room...

1:39:43.128 --> 1:39:46.103
...slight differece of temperature.

1:39:48.570 --> 1:39:54.095
and heavy rain, two months later
on the other side of the world...

1:39:54.477 --> 1:39:59.704
...that Brazilian boiled an egg
instead of being at work

1:40:00.112 --> 1:40:03.013
He would have lost his job
in a clothing factory...

1:40:03.113 --> 1:40:05.095
...because six months earlier

1:40:05.195 --> 1:40:07.225
I would have compared
the prices of jeans...

1:40:07.325 --> 1:40:09.900
...and I will have bought the cheaper pair.

1:40:10.000 --> 1:40:12.247
As the Chinese proverb says...

1:40:12.347 --> 1:40:16.459
'A single snowflake
can bend the leaf of the bamboo.'

1:40:16.559 --> 1:40:20.894
Jeans production will have
moved to other countries.

1:40:28.439 --> 1:40:31.055
I lost every trace of Anna.

1:40:34.899 --> 1:40:36.899
I waited for her...

1:40:37.894 --> 1:40:39.894
...every day.

1:42:09.963 --> 1:42:11.963
Anna.

1:42:15.391 --> 1:42:17.391
Nemo.

1:42:26.715 --> 1:42:27.616
It's back.

1:42:27.716 --> 1:42:29.101
The fear is back.

1:42:29.201 --> 1:42:31.693
I'm sick of pills.

1:42:31.741 --> 1:42:34.925
I'm sick of doctors. It's pointless.

1:42:35.611 --> 1:42:38.207
I'll do something. I can't stand it any more.

1:42:38.307 --> 1:42:40.307
I'm afraid.

1:42:40.419 --> 1:42:42.629
I don't know what to do...

1:42:46.656 --> 1:42:48.696
I often have this dream.

1:42:49.330 --> 1:42:51.370
It's a prehistoric time.

1:42:52.818 --> 1:42:55.113
I can hear you screaming...

1:43:06.429 --> 1:43:08.429
I chased the bear.

1:43:08.879 --> 1:43:11.429
And you're not afraid anymore.

1:43:11.583 --> 1:43:13.583
But when I wake up...

1:43:15.325 --> 1:43:17.325
When I wake up...

1:43:17.487 --> 1:43:19.487
...there's no bear...

1:43:20.370 --> 1:43:22.665
...but you're still afraid.

1:43:22.874 --> 1:43:24.874
I'm not a bear hunter

1:43:25.796 --> 1:43:29.470
I'm an executive of a plant that
manufactures photocopy machines...

1:43:29.570 --> 1:43:31.695
...who just quit his job.

1:43:32.764 --> 1:43:34.764
I don't dare to move.

1:43:35.774 --> 1:43:37.774
I don't live

1:43:38.449 --> 1:43:40.574
All of I do is a disaster

1:43:43.206 --> 1:43:46.812
I would so love to be able
to chase the bear away...

1:43:46.912 --> 1:43:50.312
...and for you not to be afraid anymore.

1:43:53.008 --> 1:43:56.068
To what extent are our fears innate?

1:43:57.423 --> 1:43:59.992
