in an incubator,

1:44:00.092 --> 1:44:05.786
and then, above the baby birds
pass a form simulating a goose in flight...

1:44:05.886 --> 1:44:08.651
...the birds strech their necks and call out

1:44:08.751 --> 1:44:12.249
But if we invert the direction
of the silhouette,

1:44:12.349 --> 1:44:14.460
it conjures the shape of a falcon.

1:44:14.560 --> 1:44:17.432
The response of the baby birds
is immediate.

1:44:17.532 --> 1:44:21.485
They will crouch and fear, though
they've never before seen a falcon.

1:44:21.585 --> 1:44:23.709
Without any instruction,

1:44:24.532 --> 1:44:27.677
an innate fear helps them to survive.

1:44:29.127 --> 1:44:31.127
But in humans...

1:44:31.346 --> 1:44:33.811
...to what ancient dangers...

1:44:34.024 --> 1:44:37.169
...might our innate fears correspond?

1:45:15.026 --> 1:45:18.507
NEMO... TURN AROUND...

1:45:30.408 --> 1:45:31.891
Hey.

1:45:31.991 --> 1:45:33.643
Hey.

1:45:33.743 --> 1:45:35.743
Excuse me.

1:46:19.878 --> 1:46:21.878
Remember...

1:46:22.985 --> 1:46:24.985
Remember.

1:47:38.910 --> 1:47:40.910
Honey, it's me.

1:48:57.398 --> 1:48:59.778
Did Elise die or didn't she?

1:49:00.729 --> 1:49:02.729
I don't get it.

1:49:02.828 --> 1:49:06.993
You can't have had children
