2:15:46.336 --> 2:15:50.231
I'd like the address to 1235811321.

2:15:51.228 --> 2:15:53.228
One moment please.

2:15:54.243 --> 2:15:56.443
12358 Alleway Street.

2:16:24.862 --> 2:16:26.862
Hello, Nemo.

2:16:27.082 --> 2:16:29.133
I'm glad you found me.

2:16:29.791 --> 2:16:32.703
All of this must seem
very complicated to you,

2:16:32.803 --> 2:16:35.523
but it's simpler than you think.

2:16:35.869 --> 2:16:39.014
Careful with the chair.
It is damaged.

2:16:44.876 --> 2:16:48.093
Are you alright?
- I'm fine.

2:16:50.247 --> 2:16:52.462
I should have warned you earlier but...

2:16:52.562 --> 2:16:55.297
I couldn't because of the transcript.

2:16:55.397 --> 2:16:56.912
The transcript?

2:16:57.012 --> 2:17:00.244
The text of our conversation.

2:17:02.569 --> 2:17:06.224
You can you hear me.
- What you are living now...

2:17:06.324 --> 2:17:08.324
...is the past.

2:17:08.927 --> 2:17:10.927
At least, for me.

2:17:12.641 --> 2:17:14.641
I am you...

2:17:15.005 --> 2:17:17.530
...70 years older.

2:17:19.201 --> 2:17:23.451
Everything you say, I said
myself when I was young.

2:17:23.506 --> 2:17:27.158
I only had to transcribe our conversation.

2:17:27.905 --> 2:17:30.171
It's all written right here.

2:17:30.271 --> 2:17:32.271
I can't...
- Believe it?

2:17:34.046 --> 2:17:36.046
For me...

2:17:36.270 --> 2:17:38.475
...time is inverted.

2:17:39.191 --> 2:17:41.652
I start at the end of the story...

2:17:41.752 --> 2:17:44.387
...and go toward the beginning.

2:17:44.633 --> 2:17:46.166
I don't understand.

2:17:46.266 --> 2:17:48.266
In this life here,

2:17:48.600 --> 2:17:50.756
you don't exist.

2:17:50.756 --> 2:17:52.756
I don't know why...

2:17:52.991 --> 2:17:55.217
Only the Architect knows.

2:17:56.855 --> 2:17:58.855
The Architect?

2:17:59.002 --> 2:18:01.002
The child...

2:18:01.373 --> 2:18:04.137
The one running after the train.

2:18:05.874 --> 2:18:08.594
Maybe your parents never met.

2:18:12.862 --> 2:18:17.714
Maybe your father died
in a sledging accident.

2:18:19.424 --> 2:18:21.656
Maybe you were one of the vast majority...

2:18:21.756 --> 2:18:27.366
...of those whose genetic code did not
reach its final destination.

2:18:29.895 --> 2:18:31.895
Maybe when she died...

2:18:32.404 --> 2:18:34.229
A prehistoric woman...

2:18:34.329 --> 2:18:39.089
She rolled off the line of heritance
to which you belong.

2:18:39.686 --> 2:18:41.686
So for this world...

2:18:44.212 --> 2:18:46.480
You don't exist.

2:18:47.980 --> 2:18:51.295
If the Anna's calculations are correct,

2:18:51.646 --> 2:18:58.255
you need to stay alive
untill 2092, February 12.

2:18:59.168 --> 2:19:02.001
5:50 AM.

2:19:34.522 --> 2:19:36.972
I'm sorry, I don't know how long
we haven't been recording.

2:19:37.072 --> 2:19:40.897
I have to submit my story
by tomorrow morning.

2:19:41.902 --> 2:19:45.387
Everything that you say is contradictory.

2:19:45.683 --> 2:19:49.994
You can't have been in one place
and another at the same time.

2:19:50.094 --> 2:19:54.284
You mean to say we have to make choices?

2:19:54.761 --> 2:19:57.396
Of all those lives,
which one...

2:19:57.781 --> 2:20:00.076
Which one is the right one?

2:20:00.114 --> 2:20:03.801
Each of these lives is the right one.

2:20:05.424 --> 2:20:10.109
Every path is the right path.

2:20:13.675 --> 2:20:17.974
'Everything could have been
anything else...

2:20:19.407 --> 2:20:23.944
...and it would have just as much meaning.'

2:20:26.129 --> 2:20:28.522
Tennessee Williams.

2:20:30.273 --> 2:20:32.529
You're too young for that.

2:20:32.892 --> 2:20:35.952
You can't be dead and still be here.

2:20:36.169 --> 2:20:38.169
You can't not exist.

2:20:43.950 --> 2:20:46.160
Is there life after death?

2:20:48.993 --> 2:20:50.993
After death...

2:20:53.990 --> 2:20:59.959
How can you be so sure you even exist?

2:21:10.108 --> 2:21:12.813
You don't exist.

2:21:14.346 --> 2:21:16.346
Neither do I.

2:21:19.119 --> 2:21:25.394
We only live in the imagination
of a nine year old child.

2:21:26.210 --> 2:21:30.448
We are imagined by a nine year old child,

2:21:31.373 --> 2:21:34.307
faced with an impossible choice.

2:21:44.042 --> 2:21:46.042
Run. Run.

2:21:51.663 --> 2:21:53.663
Nemo.

2:21:58.487 --> 2:22:00.487
Run.

2:22:04.836 --> 2:22:06.836
Run, Nemo.

2:22:08.902 --> 2:22:10.902
Nemo.

2:22:19.034 --> 2:22:20.915
I love you.

2:22:21.015 --> 2:22:23.015
Anna.

2:22:35.164 --> 2:22:37.164
Nemo.

2:22:45.779 --> 2:22:47.779
You're the one I love.

2:23:03.296 --> 2:23:05.296
In chess,

2:23:06.847 --> 2:23:09.563
it's called Zugzwang,

2:23:11.131 --> 2:23:13.526
when the only viable move...

2:23:19.022 --> 2:23:21.056
...is not to move.

2:23:30.939 --> 2:23:32.939
Come see.

2:23:56.209 --> 2:23:57.944
It's the sea.

2:23:58.044 --> 2:24:01.011
The child is taking it apart.

2:24:02.376 --> 2:24:04.671
He doesn't need it anymore.

2:24:05.851 --> 2:24:09.626
Before, he was unable to make a choice...

2:24:10.542 --> 2:24:13.681
'cause he didn't know what would happen.

2:24:13.781 --> 2:24:16.756
Now that he knows what will happen,

2:24:18.754 --> 2:24:21.355
he is unable to make a choice.

2:25:27.023 --> 2:25:29.023
Thank you, thank you.

2:25:29.115 --> 2:25:31.115
Thank you.

2:26:06.410 --> 2:26:12.019
This is the most beautiful day of my life.

2:26:21.244 --> 2:26:23.244
Anna.

2:26:25.904 --> 2:26:27.904
Anna.
